<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima,
                                    Peru</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-13"><hi rend="italic">September 13,
                                    1895</hi></date>. (Received October 4.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 243.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the claim known as the
                            Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon, I have the honor to report I
                            called the attention of the new Government here to this long-pending
                            case, as per copy of note inclosed.</p>
                        <p>I respectfully asked the new minister for foreign relations, Dr. Porras,
                            to be so kind as to present this case to the consideration of the
                            Peruvian Congress, now in session, that it might receive its early
                            attention.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 243.]</seg></opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Porras</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-13"><hi rend="italic">September 13,
                                        1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Minister</hi>: I beg to again call the
                                attention of your excellency’s Government most respectfully to the
                                many notes from this legation regarding the claim of American
                                citizens against Peru known as the Hydrographic Commission of the
                                Amazon, and the unusual delay in its settlement.</p>
                            <p>I express the hope, Mr. Minister, that you will be so kind as to
                                present this claim to the consideration of the present Congress,
                                that it may receive its early attention.</p>
                            <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>